<div dir="ltr">Kenneth,<div><br></div><div>I&#39;ve built ompi w/ clang on other platforms before (incl. MacOSX Mountain Lion), but not on OpenBSD.</div><div>I just now ran tests on OpenBSD-5.2/i386 and OpenBSD-5.2/amd64, using Clang-3.1.</div>

<div style>Unfortunately, there is a mass of linker error building <a href="http://libmpi_cxx.la">libmpi_cxx.la</a> (on both systems)</div><div style>I am trying again with --disable-mpi-cxx and will report my results later.</div>
<div style><br></div><div><div>Also, I had no problem with llvm-gcc on OpenBSD-5.2/i386; only on amd64 did I see a problem.</div><div><br></div></div><div>-Paul</div>
